data.content:
**Every synchronous call in your repository will throw at runtime in .NET 11.** The EF Core 11 Cosmos DB provider has **fully removed** sync I/O — the `.NET 10 opt-in no longer exists`.

Affected methods in your code:

| Breaks | Fix |
|--------|-----|
| `ToList()` | `await ToListAsync()` |
| `First(...)` | `await FirstAsync(...)` |
| `Count()` | `await CountAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `await SaveChangesAsync()` |

Your repository must become fully async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
        => await _context.Products.ToListAsync();

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
        => await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
        => await _context.Products.CountAsync();

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

All callers up the chain must also be updated to `await` these methods. There is **no workaround** — the sync-over-async opt-in was removed entirely in EF Core 11.
